<HEADLINE> Central Government Exhibits Deep Concern about Bird Flu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 30 (Xinhua) -- The Central Government and
relevant departments in Guangdong Province have tightened
quarantine controls and offered active assistance to Hong Kong in
the battle against bird flu, according to Foreign Ministry
spokesman Tang Guoqiang.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at today's regularly scheduled press conference, Tang
said the fact that relevant departments recently detected bird flu
in Hong Kong has attracted great attention from the Government of
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) and all
sectors of society. He said the HKSAR government has adopted
"very resolute" measures to detect potential sources of the virus.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation suspended all exports of live chickens to Hong Kong
for a seven day period beginning on December 24.
</P>
<P>
He said the Ministry of Agriculture has also sent experts to
investigate the situation concerning bird flu in Guangdong
Province which neighbors Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Tang said that no cases of bird flu have been detected in
inland areas.  
</P>
